metadata.title: Cirrus SR22
aws::graph::propositions: Cirrus SR22 Variants
SR22 is the original version of the Cirrus SR22.
SR22 G2 is an improved variant of the Cirrus SR22 introduced in 2004.
SR22 Turbo G2 was announced by Cirrus in July 2006.
SR22 Turbo G2 is a turbo normalized variant of the Cirrus SR22.
Some initial limited models of SR22 Turbo G2 were identified as SR22 G2 SEs.
SR22 G2 SE stands for "Signature Edition".
SR22 G2 SEs were equipped with additional features.
Additional features of SR22 G2 SEs included an unequally painted exterior.
Additional features of SR22 G2 SEs included black leather seats.
Additional features of SR22 G2 SEs included the signatures of Cirrus founders Dale and Alan Klapmeier on the cowling.
The signatures on the SR22 G2 SEs marked the 22nd anniversary of Cirrus's founding.
Dale Klapmeier is a founder of Cirrus.
Alan Klapmeier is a founder of Cirrus.
SR22TN is a version with a Tornado Alley turbo-normalizing kit.
The Tornado Alley turbo-normalizing kit is added to the Continental IO-550-N engine.
The Continental IO-550-N engine with the turbo-normalizing kit produces 310 hp (231 kW).
SR22 G3 was launched in April 2007.
SR22 G3 has an increased range compared to previous variants.
SR22 G3 has increased fuel capacity from 81 to 92 U.S. gallons.

text:
## Variants

SR22
Original version
SR22 G2
Improved variant introduced in 2004
SR22 Turbo G2
In July 2006, Cirrus announced a turbo normalized SR22. Some initial limited models were identified as SR22 G2 SEs (for "Signature Edition")equipped with additional features including an unequally painted exterior, black leather seats, and the signatures of Cirrus founders Dale and Alan Klapmeier on the cowling, marking the 22nd anniversary of the company's founding.
SR22TN
Version with a Tornado Alley turbo-normalizing kit added to the Continental IO-550-N engine producing 310 hp (231 kW).
SR22 G3
Launched in April 2007, the SR22 G3 variant has an increased range and fuel capacity, from 81 to 92 U.S.
